## 🏗️ Infrastructure Files



### Kubernetes Manifests



#### Base Infrastructure (`k8s/base/`)

- `hpa.yaml` - Main application HPA
- `postgres-read-replicas.yaml` - PostgreSQL HA with read replicas
- `redis-sentinel.yaml` - Redis HA with Sentinel
- `temporal-worker.yaml` - Temporal worker with HPA
- `resource-quotas.yaml` - Namespace quotas and limits
- `vpa.yaml` - Vertical Pod Autoscaler configurations
- `cluster-autoscaler.yaml` - Cluster-level autoscaling



#### Microservices (`k8s/emergent-services/`)

- `hpa-microservices.yaml` - HPA for all 8 microservices
- `deployments-microservices.yaml` - Microservice deployments
- `services-microservices.yaml` - Microservice services and PVCs



#### Load Testing (`k8s/load-testing/`)

- `load-test.js` - k6 load testing script
- `README.md` - Testing guide
- `test-data/users.json` - Test user data
- `test-data/workflows.json` - Test workflow data



## 🎯 Quick Start



### 1. Review Documentation
```bash
# Read implementation summary

cat SCALING_ARCHITECTURE_IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md



# Review architecture

cat SCALING_ARCHITECTURE_REPORT.md
```



### 2. Deploy Infrastructure
```bash
# Prerequisites

kubectl apply -f https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/metrics-server/releases/latest/download/components.yaml



# Phase 1: Namespace and quotas

kubectl apply -f k8s/base/namespace.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/base/resource-quotas.yaml



# Phase 2: Database layer

kubectl apply -f k8s/base/postgres.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/base/postgres-read-replicas.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/base/redis-sentinel.yaml



# Phase 3: Applications

kubectl apply -f k8s/base/deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/emergent-services/deployments-microservices.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/emergent-services/services-microservices.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/base/temporal-worker.yaml



# Phase 4: Auto-scaling

kubectl apply -f k8s/base/hpa.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/emergent-services/hpa-microservices.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/base/vpa.yaml
kubectl apply -f k8s/base/cluster-autoscaler.yaml
```



### 3. Validate Deployment
```bash
# Check HPA status

kubectl get hpa -n project-ai



# Check pod health

kubectl get pods -n project-ai



# Check resource usage

kubectl top pods -n project-ai
kubectl top nodes
```



### 4. Run Load Tests
```bash
# Baseline test

k6 run --vus 50 --duration 10m k8s/load-testing/load-test.js



# Monitor scaling

watch kubectl get hpa -n project-ai
```



## 📊 What's Implemented



### Auto-Scaling

- ✅ 11 services with HPA (CPU + Memory metrics)
- ✅ 7 services with VPA (resource recommendations)
- ✅ Cluster autoscaler (node-level scaling)
- ✅ Custom metrics support (requires Prometheus adapter)



### Database Scaling

- ✅ PostgreSQL: 1 primary + 2 read replicas
- ✅ PgBouncer: 2-8 pods (auto-scaled connection pooling)
- ✅ Redis: Master + 2 slaves + 3 sentinels
- ✅ Automatic failover with Sentinel



### Resource Management

- ✅ Resource quotas for all namespaces
- ✅ Limit ranges for containers and pods
- ✅ Priority classes for workload prioritization
- ✅ Network policies for segmentation



### Testing & Validation

- ✅ k6 load testing framework
- ✅ 5 test scenarios (baseline, stress, spike, soak, breakpoint)
- ✅ Monitoring integration
- ✅ Results template



## 📈 Scaling Capabilities

| Capability | Min | Max | Auto-Scale |
|------------|-----|-----|------------|
| Application Pods | 3 | 10 | ✅ |
| Microservice Pods | 1-3 | 8-25 | ✅ |
| Worker Pods | 3 | 30 | ✅ |
| Database Connections | - | 1000 | ✅ |
| Total Pods | ~15 | 180+ | ✅ |
| CPU Cores | 8.5 | 95 | ✅ |
| Memory (GB) | 15 | 175 | ✅ |
| Cluster Nodes | - | - | ✅ |



## 💰 Cost Impact

| Configuration | CPU | Memory | Monthly Cost |
|---------------|-----|--------|--------------|
| Minimum | 8.5 cores | 15 GB | ~$1,100 |
| Average | 30 cores | 60 GB | ~$3,150 |
| Maximum | 95 cores | 175 GB | ~$9,300 |

**Optimization Potential:** 45-50% cost reduction



